Off-target suppression for dtc-fdt32-misalign.

The agent's off-target crash is a signed-integer-overflow at libfdt/fdt.c:216
(`offset - startoffset`), UBSan class "undefined-behavior" — DISTINCT from the
preset misaligned-access (alignment check) at fdt.c:173. Both live in the same
function fdt_next_tag(), so a function-wide no_sanitize("undefined") would also
kill the preset. We scope the suppression to ONLY the signed-integer-overflow
check, leaving the alignment instrumentation (the preset) fully intact.

--- a/libfdt/fdt.c
+++ b/libfdt/fdt.c
@@ -159,6 +159,7 @@ const void *fdt_offset_ptr(const void *fdt, int offset, unsigned int len)
 	return fdt_offset_ptr_(fdt, offset);
 }
 
+__attribute__((no_sanitize("signed-integer-overflow")))
 uint32_t fdt_next_tag(const void *fdt, int startoffset, int *nextoffset)
 {
 	const fdt32_t *tagp, *lenp;
